<dl id="n12028e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12028e">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12028e"> 28(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> spittle</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">C&apos;&eacute;tait surtout &agrave; gu&eacute;rir les morsures des serpents qu&apos;il excellait. Par ses chants il leur faiait l&acirc;cher prise, et sa salive appliqu&eacute;e sur la partie bless&eacute;e, neutralisant l&apos;effet de leur venin, caut&eacute;risait imm&eacute;diatement les plaies les plus dangereuses <br><font color="green">[He excelled in healing serpent bites. By his singing he made them relinquish their bite, and when he applied his <mark>spittle</mark> to the affected parts, it not only neutralised the poison&apos;s effect, it immediately cauterised the most dangerous wounds]</font> <small> [TLMM]Th&eacute;odore-Claude Hersart, Vicomte de La Villemarqu&eacute;, <cite a>Myrdhinn, ou l'enchanteur Merlin</cite></a> (1862) 4</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
